1
00:00:19,233 --> 00:00:22,108
♪

2
00:00:56,900 --> 00:00:59,108
This is the place.
I think.

3
00:00:59,192 --> 00:01:02,442
♪

4
00:01:02,525 --> 00:01:03,358
[sighs]

5
00:02:39,692 --> 00:02:41,692
-[MIYAKO] Um, hi.
-Yeah?

6
00:02:41,775 --> 00:02:45,108
I'm looking for the Nocturnal
Community Relations Division.

7
00:02:45,192 --> 00:02:47,483
I'm Miyako Arata.

8
00:02:47,567 --> 00:02:49,567
[GUARD]
Ah, so you're the new kid, huh?

9
00:02:49,650 --> 00:02:52,858
Sakaki told me you'd be by.
Please come on in.

10
00:02:52,942 --> 00:02:56,483
Follow that hallway to the end
and turn right.

11
00:02:56,567 --> 00:02:57,900
Pass the elevator hall.

12
00:02:57,983 --> 00:03:00,067
Make a turn at the corner
with the cafeteria,

13
00:03:00,150 --> 00:03:01,567
then you should see it.

14
00:03:01,650 --> 00:03:03,108
First door on the left.

15
00:03:04,733 --> 00:03:05,858
This it?

16
00:03:06,942 --> 00:03:08,567
Hi, I hope you weren't
waiting long.

17
00:03:08,650 --> 00:03:11,192
That's strange.
No one's here.

18
00:03:11,275 --> 00:03:12,108
Uh?

19
00:03:13,733 --> 00:03:14,567
[MIYAKO screams]

20
00:03:14,650 --> 00:03:16,358
[coughing]

21
00:03:19,025 --> 00:03:21,108
[THEO]
Jeez. Didn't expect that.

22
00:03:21,192 --> 00:03:23,358
Did I use the wrong stuff?

23
00:03:23,442 --> 00:03:27,483
Let's see, sulfur, aluminum,
and goat gallstones.

24
00:03:27,567 --> 00:03:29,317
Were my proportions off?

25
00:03:29,400 --> 00:03:31,817
-Um, excuse me?
-[THEO] Huh?

26
00:03:31,900 --> 00:03:35,358
Is this the Nocturnal Community
Relations Division or...

27
00:03:35,442 --> 00:03:38,358
[THEO]
It is, but who are you?

28
00:03:38,442 --> 00:03:41,067
Well, I'm supposed to be
starting here today, but---

29
00:03:41,150 --> 00:03:43,275
[THEO] Oh yes!
You're the new kid!

30
00:03:44,275 --> 00:03:47,150
I remember Reiji telling me
something about that earlier.

31
00:03:48,192 --> 00:03:49,192
[gasps]

32
00:03:50,608 --> 00:03:53,483
Nice to meet you.
I'm Theo Himeduka. I work here.

33
00:03:53,567 --> 00:03:55,900
There's no need to be formal
around here, so please,

34
00:03:55,983 --> 00:03:58,108
-call me Theo.
-If you say so.

35
00:03:58,192 --> 00:04:00,067
I used to live in Britain,

36
00:04:00,150 --> 00:04:01,525
so I'm used to first names.

37
00:04:01,608 --> 00:04:04,733
Seriously, Theo?
You did it again, didn't you?

38
00:04:04,817 --> 00:04:07,567
The smoke got all the way
to the cafeteria this time!

39
00:04:07,650 --> 00:04:09,858
-Tell me you weren't using fire.
-[THEO growls]

40
00:04:09,942 --> 00:04:13,192
The only one in the wrong here
is you, Kyouichi!

41
00:04:14,192 --> 00:04:15,192
You jerk!

42
00:04:15,275 --> 00:04:16,525
You used my photo to break up

43
00:04:16,608 --> 00:04:18,358
with your latest skank again,
didn't you?

44
00:04:18,442 --> 00:04:20,817
-Grow up!
-Oh. Secret's out.

45
00:04:20,900 --> 00:04:23,067
Listen, it's so much easier
for them

46
00:04:23,150 --> 00:04:24,650
to think I found someone else.

47
00:04:24,733 --> 00:04:26,400
[THEO]
Not for me!

48
00:04:26,483 --> 00:04:28,608
Every day there's some
angry hag on my doorstep

49
00:04:28,692 --> 00:04:30,108
giving me the side-eye!

50
00:04:30,192 --> 00:04:31,400
[KYOUICHI]
Lucky you!

51
00:04:31,483 --> 00:04:32,733
[THEO] Quit making me
clean up your mess

52
00:04:32,817 --> 00:04:34,275
after these shady trysts!

53
00:04:35,275 --> 00:04:38,275
I swear. It happens again,
you'll regret it.

54
00:04:38,358 --> 00:04:39,692
Wow, I'm an idiot.

55
00:04:39,775 --> 00:04:41,317
Do you have a cold,
Miss Himeduka?

56
00:04:41,400 --> 00:04:42,692
I thought you were
a man for a--

57
00:04:42,775 --> 00:04:44,317
What? Of course I'm a man!

58
00:04:44,400 --> 00:04:46,233
I told you to call me Theo!

59
00:04:46,317 --> 00:04:48,150
-Theo!
-[MIYAKO] Okay.

60
00:04:48,233 --> 00:04:50,733
[THEO groans]
It's really not that hard.

61
00:04:50,817 --> 00:04:52,942
Hello. This is Sakaki.
What's up?

62
00:04:54,108 --> 00:04:56,692
Yeah, Miyako's here.
The new recruit.

63
00:04:56,775 --> 00:04:58,192
Should I send him in?

64
00:05:00,733 --> 00:05:01,858
Understood.

65
00:05:01,942 --> 00:05:03,858
It's no problem,
introductions can wait.

66
00:05:03,942 --> 00:05:05,817
That's Sakaki Kyouichi.

67
00:05:05,900 --> 00:05:07,358
-He loves women and drinking.
-Right.

68
00:05:07,442 --> 00:05:08,858
-[THEO] Used to work as a host.
-Yeah.

69
00:05:08,942 --> 00:05:10,483
[THEO] Now he's the
shift leader of the division.

70
00:05:10,567 --> 00:05:12,942
Never know it by looking at him.

71
00:05:13,025 --> 00:05:14,442
[MIYAKO]
Huh.

72
00:05:14,525 --> 00:05:16,358
[KYOUICHI]
Thanks for that, Theo.

73
00:05:16,442 --> 00:05:17,692
Feel free to ask us
about anything

74
00:05:17,775 --> 00:05:19,442
you don't understand, all right?

75
00:05:19,525 --> 00:05:21,817
Thank you so much.
I appreciate that.

76
00:05:21,900 --> 00:05:23,233
-[bell ringing]
-[MIYAKO] Huh?

77
00:05:23,317 --> 00:05:24,608
Well, it's 7:00.

78
00:05:24,692 --> 00:05:27,442
About time for us
to get to work, then.

79
00:05:27,525 --> 00:05:30,025
Change into the outfit
in that far-right locker.

80
00:05:30,108 --> 00:05:32,358
We'll be going outside
for your first shift.

81
00:05:34,317 --> 00:05:36,817
We spend most of our time
outside the office.

82
00:05:36,900 --> 00:05:39,025
I'll give you a nametag
to wear inside later.

83
00:05:39,108 --> 00:05:40,650
We work a different shift
than everyone else,

84
00:05:40,733 --> 00:05:41,983
so you won't use it much.

85
00:05:42,067 --> 00:05:45,358
Um, won't it be
getting dark soon?

86
00:05:45,442 --> 00:05:47,442
What part of the job
requires going out at night?

87
00:05:47,525 --> 00:05:49,733
-What were you told?
-[MIYAKO] Huh?

88
00:05:49,817 --> 00:05:52,483
Oh, um, the job description said

89
00:05:52,567 --> 00:05:54,192
"building relationships
with people of all ages

90
00:05:54,275 --> 00:05:56,483
"in various fields
and social positions.

91
00:05:56,567 --> 00:05:58,150
Also engaging in planning
and promotion."

92
00:05:58,233 --> 00:06:00,442
[THEO]
That's right. This is Shinjuku,

93
00:06:00,525 --> 00:06:02,108
where people from
several different countries

94
00:06:02,192 --> 00:06:04,650
do many different jobs
in many different places.

95
00:06:04,733 --> 00:06:06,400
[KYOUICHI] You might be
wondering what it is we do

96
00:06:06,483 --> 00:06:08,317
to make this a better place
for them to live.

97
00:06:09,317 --> 00:06:12,150
Well, figuring that out
is our job, basically.

98
00:06:13,817 --> 00:06:16,275
At least, that's what
the paperwork says.

99
00:06:16,358 --> 00:06:17,775
Is that helpful?

100
00:06:17,858 --> 00:06:20,900
Have you ever seen a youkai
or an angel or a devil?

101
00:06:20,983 --> 00:06:22,317
[MIYAKO]
Huh?

102
00:06:24,150 --> 00:06:26,858
Is this a joke, or am I supposed
to answer that seriously?

103
00:06:26,942 --> 00:06:29,233
I'll go ahead
and take that as a hard no.

104
00:06:29,317 --> 00:06:30,942
But if you were assigned here,

105
00:06:31,025 --> 00:06:32,567
it means you triggered
that little trick

106
00:06:32,650 --> 00:06:34,483
that's hidden
in the employment exam.

107
00:06:34,567 --> 00:06:37,108
[KYOUICHI] He's probably
the type who didn't notice it.

108
00:06:37,192 --> 00:06:39,608
[THEO] Well then, we'll need
to do a rite of passage.

109
00:06:39,692 --> 00:06:42,233
Huh? I don't know what
you're talking about.

110
00:06:42,317 --> 00:06:43,608
[chuckles]

111
00:06:43,692 --> 00:06:45,817
♪

112
00:06:51,525 --> 00:06:52,525
What is this place?

113
00:06:52,608 --> 00:06:55,525
Huh? Shinjuku Imperial Gardens.

114
00:06:55,608 --> 00:06:57,233
You've never been?

115
00:06:57,317 --> 00:07:00,275
Well, sure. I have but, um...

116
00:07:00,358 --> 00:07:01,692
Wait, I don't think
they allow anyone

117
00:07:01,775 --> 00:07:03,108
to go in at night, do they?

118
00:07:03,192 --> 00:07:05,942
We have to come here a lot
as part of our job,

119
00:07:06,025 --> 00:07:06,983
so we have a key.

120
00:07:07,983 --> 00:07:10,817
There's hardly any light inside,
so be careful.

121
00:07:10,900 --> 00:07:12,067
Sure, okay!

122
00:07:15,733 --> 00:07:18,442
[MIYAKO] We work in the
Imperial Gardens after hours?

123
00:07:18,525 --> 00:07:19,817
What did I sign up for?

124
00:07:19,900 --> 00:07:21,275
That looks like a good spot.

125
00:07:21,358 --> 00:07:22,983
I agree.

126
00:07:23,067 --> 00:07:24,900
The rite of passage,
you ready?

127
00:07:24,983 --> 00:07:27,775
Uh, hold on. I don't understand.

128
00:07:27,858 --> 00:07:29,525
What is this thing
you keep talking about?

129
00:07:29,608 --> 00:07:31,233
There's nothing
to be afraid of.

130
00:07:31,317 --> 00:07:33,817
Even if you scream and pass out,
I'll take care of you.

131
00:07:33,900 --> 00:07:36,650
It'll be easier to understand
if you experience the job

132
00:07:36,733 --> 00:07:37,983
rather than us explaining it.

133
00:07:40,317 --> 00:07:41,692
-Look over there.
-[MIYAKO] Huh?

134
00:07:41,775 --> 00:07:43,942
[KYOUICHI] Notice the fairy?
Between those trees.

135
00:07:44,025 --> 00:07:47,692
Uh... where?

136
00:07:47,775 --> 00:07:49,150
It's there.

137
00:07:49,233 --> 00:07:51,233
You probably can't see it
right now, though.

138
00:07:52,358 --> 00:07:54,817
Same goes for youkai,
angels, and devils.

139
00:07:54,900 --> 00:07:56,942
In fact you should assume
most of the occult creatures

140
00:07:57,025 --> 00:07:59,317
you've seen in works
of fiction actually exist.

141
00:07:59,400 --> 00:08:00,775
And, rookie,
that's the first lesson

142
00:08:00,858 --> 00:08:02,442
on our agenda for tonight.

143
00:08:02,525 --> 00:08:04,983
Okay. It's just kinda hard
to believe

144
00:08:05,067 --> 00:08:06,483
this has anything
to do with work.

145
00:08:06,567 --> 00:08:07,608
I understand.

146
00:08:07,692 --> 00:08:08,858
But it's an
important discussion

147
00:08:08,942 --> 00:08:10,608
pertaining to the job we do.

148
00:08:10,692 --> 00:08:12,942
-Theo?
-Yup, that's right.

149
00:08:16,692 --> 00:08:18,608
So, why are we spraying bushes?

150
00:08:18,692 --> 00:08:20,650
It's the Spray of Ibn Ghazi,

151
00:08:20,733 --> 00:08:24,275
a little helper for people
who can't see them normally.

152
00:08:24,358 --> 00:08:26,108
It's made from the soil
of ancient tombs,

153
00:08:26,192 --> 00:08:29,067
amaranth flowers,
and ground ivy.

154
00:08:29,150 --> 00:08:30,942
Look. There, in front of you.

155
00:08:31,942 --> 00:08:34,150
♪

156
00:08:36,900 --> 00:08:37,775
[MIYAKO]
Huh?

157
00:08:37,858 --> 00:08:39,233
Now tell me what do you see?

158
00:08:39,317 --> 00:08:41,650
[MIYAKO]
I, uh, I see a light.

159
00:08:41,733 --> 00:08:43,650
-Wait, it's changing.
-[FAIRY coughing]

160
00:08:45,275 --> 00:08:48,192
What is happening?
It's a little girl?

161
00:08:48,275 --> 00:08:51,525
And she has wings on her back.

162
00:08:51,608 --> 00:08:53,608
Is that a fairy?

163
00:08:53,692 --> 00:08:54,650
[FAIRY huffs]

164
00:08:56,942 --> 00:08:59,233
[grunting]

165
00:09:00,358 --> 00:09:01,817
[THEO]
That one was a pixie.

166
00:09:01,900 --> 00:09:03,275
You can find them everywhere.

167
00:09:05,150 --> 00:09:07,358
It's just hard to believe.

168
00:09:07,442 --> 00:09:09,567
Well, you have to believe it
if you can see it.

169
00:09:09,650 --> 00:09:11,942
Because, otherwise,
you'll just have to assume

170
00:09:12,025 --> 00:09:12,983
that you're going insane.

171
00:09:14,858 --> 00:09:15,775
[gasps]

172
00:09:15,858 --> 00:09:19,692
♪

173
00:09:19,775 --> 00:09:21,317
[hisses]

174
00:09:21,400 --> 00:09:26,400
♪

175
00:09:26,483 --> 00:09:28,233
-[thudding footsteps]
-[MIYAKO] Huh?

176
00:09:30,608 --> 00:09:34,608
[MIYAKO gasping]
What the hell is that?

177
00:09:34,692 --> 00:09:36,942
You can see without
the spray already?

178
00:09:37,025 --> 00:09:38,317
Means you've got
good instincts.

179
00:09:38,400 --> 00:09:40,483
This big boy is a Cu Sith.

180
00:09:40,567 --> 00:09:42,025
Don't worry, it's friendly.

181
00:09:42,108 --> 00:09:43,442
[MIYAKO whimpering]

182
00:09:43,525 --> 00:09:44,775
Neat, huh?

183
00:09:44,858 --> 00:09:46,442
They all have
their own unique names.

184
00:09:46,525 --> 00:09:49,067
And each falls under a certain
category of occult creature.

185
00:09:49,150 --> 00:09:51,608
Angel, Devil,
Youkai, and Fairy.

186
00:09:51,692 --> 00:09:54,025
That said, we have
a general term for them.

187
00:09:54,108 --> 00:09:55,525
We refer to
the non-human creatures

188
00:09:55,608 --> 00:09:56,858
we use in our work as...

189
00:09:56,942 --> 00:09:58,192
"Anothers."

190
00:09:59,775 --> 00:10:02,567
Wow, you don't seem
very scared.

191
00:10:02,650 --> 00:10:04,233
[MIYAKO]
Well, no.

192
00:10:04,317 --> 00:10:06,358
I'm more surprised.

193
00:10:06,442 --> 00:10:08,358
If that's all you are,
then this rite of passage

194
00:10:08,442 --> 00:10:09,608
was a big success.

195
00:10:09,692 --> 00:10:10,900
Looks like we might have
actually got

196
00:10:10,983 --> 00:10:12,442
a decent rookie this time.

197
00:10:12,525 --> 00:10:14,650
Most are usually
passed out by now.

198
00:10:14,733 --> 00:10:16,942
Or at least their legs
are too weak to stand.

199
00:10:17,025 --> 00:10:18,483
But you're doing
all right, huh?

200
00:10:18,567 --> 00:10:21,942
Yeah, but I'm still wondering
what our job is?

201
00:10:22,025 --> 00:10:24,733
[KYOUICHI] Maintaining relations
with the Anothers.

202
00:10:24,817 --> 00:10:27,858
And then, if they cause any
problems for civilians, well...

203
00:10:27,942 --> 00:10:30,733
we're the ones who
take care of it, make sense?

204
00:10:30,817 --> 00:10:33,900
As members of the Nocturnal
Community Relations Division,

205
00:10:33,983 --> 00:10:35,650
we work primarily
as public servants.

206
00:10:37,775 --> 00:10:39,525
Hmm? What's wrong?

207
00:10:39,608 --> 00:10:41,483
Nothing. Just...

208
00:10:41,567 --> 00:10:43,858
-I'm a little worried.
-Nothing to be worried about!

209
00:10:43,942 --> 00:10:46,692
If you can stay calm at the
first time of seeing Anothers,

210
00:10:46,775 --> 00:10:48,233
I'd say you're doing
pretty good!

211
00:10:48,317 --> 00:10:49,775
He's got a good point.

212
00:10:49,858 --> 00:10:51,233
Just do what you're told

213
00:10:51,317 --> 00:10:53,317
and focus on the things
you feel good about.

214
00:10:53,400 --> 00:10:55,275
We won't ask for much more
than that just yet.

215
00:10:56,775 --> 00:10:57,775
Okay.

216
00:10:57,858 --> 00:10:59,650
Miyako Arata.

217
00:10:59,733 --> 00:11:01,608
We're the Shinjuku Ward
Nocturnal Community

218
00:11:01,692 --> 00:11:03,067
Relations Division,

219
00:11:03,150 --> 00:11:04,400
and we're glad to have you.

220
00:11:08,442 --> 00:11:11,150
So here's what's on our list
of things to do tonight.

221
00:11:11,233 --> 00:11:12,817
We're investigating
some loud noises

222
00:11:12,900 --> 00:11:14,608
that have been
reported lately.

223
00:11:14,692 --> 00:11:17,817
They seem to be coming from here
in the Imperial Gardens.

224
00:11:17,900 --> 00:11:19,942
-Noises?
-Yeah.

225
00:11:20,025 --> 00:11:21,692
Since there are
no events being held,

226
00:11:21,775 --> 00:11:23,317
we don't know
where they'd be coming from.

227
00:11:23,400 --> 00:11:26,192
We were patrolling around
this area last night.

228
00:11:26,275 --> 00:11:28,775
That's where we found traces of
two different types of Anothers

229
00:11:28,858 --> 00:11:30,567
at the site
of a damaged tree.

230
00:11:31,900 --> 00:11:34,775
Analysis of both the physical
and circumstantial evidence

231
00:11:34,858 --> 00:11:37,775
leads us to believe there's some
sort of territory struggle.

232
00:11:37,858 --> 00:11:40,567
We believe it's between some
of the tengu and the angels.

233
00:11:40,650 --> 00:11:42,692
Huh? So they fight each other?

234
00:11:42,775 --> 00:11:45,442
-The Anothers, I mean.
-Oh yeah, for sure.

235
00:11:45,525 --> 00:11:47,733
The Imperial Gardens have
a lot space and greenery,

236
00:11:47,817 --> 00:11:50,858
so there are multiple types
of Anothers that live here.

237
00:11:50,942 --> 00:11:52,233
Sometimes they fight.

238
00:11:52,317 --> 00:11:55,108
[MIYAKO] Okay.
So how do we stop them?

239
00:11:55,192 --> 00:11:57,192
-Put up a barrier.
-[MIYAKO] Huh?

240
00:11:58,317 --> 00:11:59,942
Oh, you mean with,
like, talismans,

241
00:12:00,025 --> 00:12:01,775
and salt and burning sage?

242
00:12:01,858 --> 00:12:03,525
-More like that.
-[MIYAKO] Huh?

243
00:12:04,692 --> 00:12:06,233
-[MIYAKO] Tape?
-[THEO] Yup.

244
00:12:06,317 --> 00:12:08,067
It engages
the element of wind

245
00:12:08,150 --> 00:12:10,317
and adjusts the area's
dimensional phase.

246
00:12:10,400 --> 00:12:12,483
That creates a fairly
powerful barrier

247
00:12:12,567 --> 00:12:14,108
which can block out
most noises.

248
00:12:14,192 --> 00:12:16,108
Theo made it himself.

249
00:12:16,192 --> 00:12:18,192
The other wards
are using it, too.

250
00:12:18,275 --> 00:12:20,942
Hey, did you find out
about Sendagaya Gate?

251
00:12:21,025 --> 00:12:22,817
[KYOUICHI] I spoke
to Shibuya's division earlier,

252
00:12:22,900 --> 00:12:24,525
so I'm sure it's handled.

253
00:12:24,608 --> 00:12:25,942
[MIYAKO]
Ah!

254
00:12:26,025 --> 00:12:28,025
The Gardens run into
Shibuya Ward, don't they?

255
00:12:28,108 --> 00:12:29,150
Here you go.

256
00:12:30,317 --> 00:12:31,817
Newb.

257
00:12:31,900 --> 00:12:33,817
We'll split up
into two groups

258
00:12:33,900 --> 00:12:35,650
and make barriers with this.

259
00:12:35,733 --> 00:12:37,025
-Sound good?
-Yeah.

260
00:12:37,108 --> 00:12:39,025
[tape ripping]

261
00:12:42,317 --> 00:12:45,400
Nice job.
I'll finish this one.

262
00:12:45,483 --> 00:12:47,275
Can you go work
on that forest over there?

263
00:12:47,358 --> 00:12:50,483
Just run the tape along
the trees on the left side.

264
00:12:50,567 --> 00:12:51,567
[MIYAKO]
Roger that.

265
00:12:56,317 --> 00:12:57,233
[sighs]

266
00:12:58,233 --> 00:13:00,483
[MIYAKO] Can this really create
a strong enough barrier?

267
00:13:00,567 --> 00:13:02,108
[leaves rustling]

268
00:13:07,317 --> 00:13:12,150
[screeching]

269
00:13:12,233 --> 00:13:13,692
[inaudible dialogue]

270
00:13:16,150 --> 00:13:18,942
[TAROUBOU]
Oh, my winged beauty.

271
00:13:19,025 --> 00:13:20,442
My beloved Adiel.

272
00:13:21,525 --> 00:13:24,567
I feel so powerless having only
one place where I can meet you.

273
00:13:24,650 --> 00:13:25,775
[ADIEL]
It doesn't matter to me

274
00:13:25,858 --> 00:13:27,817
where we need
to meet, my Taroubou.

275
00:13:27,900 --> 00:13:29,150
As long as you're safe.

276
00:13:30,192 --> 00:13:32,067
I long for a life in the sky.

277
00:13:32,150 --> 00:13:34,192
-The two of us together.
-As do I.

278
00:13:34,275 --> 00:13:36,525
All I want is to fly
with you forever!

279
00:13:36,608 --> 00:13:37,983
Then let's do it!

280
00:13:38,067 --> 00:13:39,858
I know the others
will never accept us,

281
00:13:39,942 --> 00:13:41,525
but who cares?

282
00:13:41,608 --> 00:13:44,608
Really? I'm so happy!

283
00:13:44,692 --> 00:13:47,150
[ADIEL gasps]
But no,

284
00:13:47,233 --> 00:13:49,733
I could never leave
my dear sister behind.

285
00:13:49,817 --> 00:13:52,233
[TAROUBOU inhales sharply]
I'm sorry.

286
00:13:56,275 --> 00:13:58,317
I'm afraid
it's time for me to go.

287
00:13:58,400 --> 00:13:59,942
[ADIEL]
So soon, my love?

288
00:14:00,025 --> 00:14:02,483
I want to spend
my future with you.

289
00:14:02,567 --> 00:14:04,650
Promise me you'll think
about it. Okay?

290
00:14:06,650 --> 00:14:07,900
[gasps softly]

291
00:14:13,733 --> 00:14:15,525
-[KYOUICHI] That's an angel.
-[MIYAKO] Uh...

292
00:14:15,608 --> 00:14:17,858
And the other one
was a tengu.

293
00:14:17,942 --> 00:14:19,442
It's rare
to see them together.

294
00:14:19,525 --> 00:14:21,317
Rarer that they'd stand
so close.

295
00:14:21,400 --> 00:14:22,858
That's fascinating.

296
00:14:22,942 --> 00:14:25,733
I thought they were having
an argument at first.

297
00:14:25,817 --> 00:14:27,317
[MIYAKO]
But then it quickly changed.

298
00:14:27,400 --> 00:14:28,692
-[booming]
-[MIYAKO gasps]

299
00:14:29,692 --> 00:14:31,358
[FOLCIEL]
There you are, Taroubou!

300
00:14:31,442 --> 00:14:33,233
I am Adiel's sister, Folciel,

301
00:14:33,317 --> 00:14:35,483
and I know very well
that you've been deceiving her!

302
00:14:35,567 --> 00:14:37,608
I've come here tonight
to destroy you!

303
00:14:37,692 --> 00:14:40,358
Wait, please.
You must've misunderstood!

304
00:14:42,150 --> 00:14:43,692
You won't get away!

305
00:14:48,025 --> 00:14:49,692
Hold it right there!

306
00:14:49,775 --> 00:14:51,108
Father, what are you doing?

307
00:14:51,192 --> 00:14:53,400
Stay right there, Taroubou!

308
00:14:53,483 --> 00:14:56,233
How dare you accuse
the son of Yotsuya Fudoubou!

309
00:14:56,317 --> 00:14:57,858
You should all know better!

310
00:14:57,942 --> 00:15:00,025
Did you think I'd stay back
and allow you to kidnap him?

311
00:15:00,108 --> 00:15:02,233
I know exactly
what you monsters are up to!

312
00:15:02,317 --> 00:15:03,608
[grunting]

313
00:15:03,692 --> 00:15:04,650
No way!

314
00:15:05,650 --> 00:15:07,942
I hope they both
settle down on their own.

315
00:15:08,025 --> 00:15:09,817
-Huh?
-[water sloshing]

316
00:15:11,775 --> 00:15:14,233
He's taking Adiel!
No, you don't!

317
00:15:15,817 --> 00:15:17,775
That's strange!
What are they trying to do?

318
00:15:22,400 --> 00:15:24,317
Wait, Adiel!
We're coming for you!

319
00:15:24,400 --> 00:15:26,900
Theo! They might be
leaving the park!

320
00:15:26,983 --> 00:15:29,650
What? How is that possible?

321
00:15:29,733 --> 00:15:30,983
[KYOUICHI]
Hell if I know!

322
00:15:31,067 --> 00:15:32,358
[ringing]

323
00:15:35,025 --> 00:15:36,483
[MAN A] Yes, this is
the Nocturnal Community

324
00:15:36,567 --> 00:15:38,025
-Relations Division?
-[KYOUICHI] It's Sakaki!

325
00:15:38,108 --> 00:15:39,525
The Anothers are leaving!

326
00:15:39,608 --> 00:15:42,150
They're heading to the city.
We're gonna follow 'em!

327
00:15:42,233 --> 00:15:44,733
Thanks for the update!
You guys be safe.

328
00:15:46,400 --> 00:15:47,400
[keypad beeping]

329
00:15:47,483 --> 00:15:49,983
-[panting]
-[phone ringing]

330
00:15:50,067 --> 00:15:51,525
[MAN B over phone]
Yes?

331
00:15:51,608 --> 00:15:53,983
[MAN A] This is Shinjuku
Nocturnal Community Relations.

332
00:15:55,025 --> 00:15:56,942
I was just informed
some of our staff

333
00:15:57,025 --> 00:15:58,775
are trailing some Anothers.

334
00:15:58,858 --> 00:15:59,983
[MAN B]
And?

335
00:16:00,067 --> 00:16:01,233
[MAN A]
They may be heading your way.

336
00:16:01,317 --> 00:16:02,983
Just wanted to give you
a heads up.

337
00:16:03,067 --> 00:16:04,067
[phone disconnects]

338
00:16:04,150 --> 00:16:08,192
♪

339
00:16:08,275 --> 00:16:09,733
[inhales sharply]

340
00:16:10,983 --> 00:16:11,942
[TENGU grunt]

341
00:16:12,025 --> 00:16:14,442
Adiel! Get away
from that tengu!

342
00:16:14,525 --> 00:16:16,567
Sister, please,
you have to stop this!

343
00:16:16,650 --> 00:16:19,233
Oh, so you refuse? Fine!

344
00:16:19,317 --> 00:16:20,275
[ADIEL gasps]

345
00:16:21,442 --> 00:16:22,358
[CROWD screaming]

346
00:16:26,525 --> 00:16:28,692
Is this the noise
they were complaining about?

347
00:16:28,775 --> 00:16:30,858
♪

348
00:16:35,775 --> 00:16:36,942
[panting]

349
00:16:37,025 --> 00:16:39,692
[THEO]
Wow, there are so many of them!

350
00:16:39,775 --> 00:16:42,108
♪

351
00:16:52,400 --> 00:16:54,483
[cell phone buzzing]

352
00:16:54,567 --> 00:16:56,400
-This is Sakaki!
-[THEO] City Hall!

353
00:16:56,483 --> 00:16:57,942
Get over here right away!

354
00:16:58,025 --> 00:17:00,358
They're all fighting each other
in the People's Plaza!

355
00:17:00,442 --> 00:17:01,275
Hurry it up!

356
00:17:01,358 --> 00:17:03,483
♪

357
00:17:07,108 --> 00:17:08,650
We're here.
How's it looking?

358
00:17:08,733 --> 00:17:10,775
Dirty looks and small spats.

359
00:17:10,858 --> 00:17:12,733
This could go on till morning.

360
00:17:13,983 --> 00:17:16,692
-What is it?
-You might be wrong.

361
00:17:16,775 --> 00:17:18,858
I don't think they're fighting
over territory.

362
00:17:20,400 --> 00:17:22,025
I didn't say it was fact!

363
00:17:22,108 --> 00:17:24,817
Angels and tengu don't get along
and I made a guess, so sue me!

364
00:17:24,900 --> 00:17:26,775
What? Are you serious?

365
00:17:28,150 --> 00:17:30,608
[MIYAKO] I guess that means
none of them know.

366
00:17:30,692 --> 00:17:31,858
-[THEO] Know what?
-Those two.

367
00:17:31,942 --> 00:17:33,358
I just saw them in the park.

368
00:17:33,442 --> 00:17:35,317
Taroubou and Adiel.

369
00:17:35,400 --> 00:17:37,025
They're in love with each other!

370
00:17:39,692 --> 00:17:41,733
[BOTH]
Taroubou. Who?

371
00:17:41,817 --> 00:17:43,733
The tengu who was
with the angel.

372
00:17:45,567 --> 00:17:47,942
All right, hold on.
I'm not following you at all.

373
00:17:48,025 --> 00:17:50,483
You just saw them
standing next to each other.

374
00:17:50,567 --> 00:17:51,942
How do you know?

375
00:17:52,025 --> 00:17:53,775
-Well, because I heard---
-[THEO] Run, you idiot!

376
00:17:55,150 --> 00:17:56,358
[crash]

377
00:17:56,442 --> 00:17:58,692
Arata! Are you okay?

378
00:17:58,775 --> 00:18:00,233
That hurt.

379
00:18:00,317 --> 00:18:01,858
But, yeah, I think I'm fine.

380
00:18:03,775 --> 00:18:05,983
So I got a human involved.
I'm sorry.

381
00:18:07,025 --> 00:18:08,608
And now you want
to fight us too?

382
00:18:08,692 --> 00:18:09,817
[FUDOUBOU gasps]

383
00:18:09,900 --> 00:18:10,983
[FOLCIEL]
Please forgive her.

384
00:18:11,067 --> 00:18:12,275
She never meant to hurt the boy.

385
00:18:12,358 --> 00:18:14,025
The angels
are attacking us, too?

386
00:18:14,108 --> 00:18:16,858
You must understand,
we do not wish to fight you.

387
00:18:16,942 --> 00:18:18,567
[KYOUICHI] They're not gonna
give up, are they?

388
00:18:18,650 --> 00:18:20,192
[MIYAKO]
Huh?

389
00:18:20,275 --> 00:18:21,900
You might want
to step back, Arata.

390
00:18:21,983 --> 00:18:23,900
This next move is going
to hit them pretty hard.

391
00:18:23,983 --> 00:18:25,733
[MIYAKO]
But why?

392
00:18:25,817 --> 00:18:27,483
There's no need
to go easy on them!

393
00:18:27,567 --> 00:18:28,775
Hold on. We--

394
00:18:28,858 --> 00:18:29,775
You want a fight?

395
00:18:29,858 --> 00:18:31,067
[MIYAKO]
Why?

396
00:18:31,150 --> 00:18:35,358
♪

397
00:18:35,442 --> 00:18:37,858
[MIYAKO]
Why is this happening?

398
00:18:37,942 --> 00:18:39,483
-Now, Theo!
-On it!

399
00:18:40,525 --> 00:18:43,150
[MIYAKO] No one is listening!
No one's being heard!

400
00:18:43,233 --> 00:18:44,858
♪

401
00:18:44,942 --> 00:18:46,108
[loud bang]

402
00:18:46,192 --> 00:18:49,233
[ALL coughing]

403
00:18:55,942 --> 00:18:58,525
Are you out of your mind?
What are you doing?

404
00:18:58,608 --> 00:19:01,525
Listen! They were trying
to apologize!

405
00:19:01,608 --> 00:19:03,275
Yotsuya Fudoubou and Folciel

406
00:19:03,358 --> 00:19:06,108
both said they had
no intentions of hurting me!

407
00:19:06,192 --> 00:19:07,900
Wait. Did you say...

408
00:19:09,858 --> 00:19:11,775
You guys need to relax, too!

409
00:19:11,858 --> 00:19:13,150
Adiel's not in any danger!

410
00:19:13,233 --> 00:19:16,483
You're kidding me. No way!

411
00:19:16,567 --> 00:19:19,025
So are you talking to them?

412
00:19:19,108 --> 00:19:20,650
[MIYAKO]
Huh?

413
00:19:20,733 --> 00:19:22,025
I'm just repeating
what they said

414
00:19:22,108 --> 00:19:23,775
when they were right
in front of you.

415
00:19:23,858 --> 00:19:25,483
Did you not hear them
or something?

416
00:19:25,567 --> 00:19:27,775
We can't understand
their language!

417
00:19:27,858 --> 00:19:29,858
Don't act surprised!
They're Anothers!

418
00:19:29,942 --> 00:19:31,942
How the hell are we supposed
to know what they're saying?

419
00:19:32,025 --> 00:19:35,775
It's no different than trying to
understand your dog or your cat!

420
00:19:35,858 --> 00:19:37,483
[KYOUICHI]
Where did they find this kid?

421
00:19:37,567 --> 00:19:38,692
[THEO]
Mnh-mnh.

422
00:19:38,775 --> 00:19:41,025
So then, you can
understand our words?

423
00:19:41,108 --> 00:19:43,900
Hello. Would you mind
telling me who you are?

424
00:19:43,983 --> 00:19:46,067
Just an employee

425
00:19:46,150 --> 00:19:48,775
of the Shinjuku
Ward Office, ma'am.

426
00:19:48,858 --> 00:19:49,942
-[ADIEL] Sister!
-[MIYAKO gasps]

427
00:19:53,358 --> 00:19:54,775
[FOLCIEL and FUDOUBOU]
Wait, What?

428
00:19:54,858 --> 00:19:56,150
You want to elope?

429
00:19:57,400 --> 00:19:59,483
[ALL ANOTHERS murmuring]

430
00:19:59,567 --> 00:20:01,733
-[ANGEL A] An angel?
-[TENGU A] And a tengu?

431
00:20:01,817 --> 00:20:03,025
[TENGU B]
This is unheard of!

432
00:20:03,108 --> 00:20:04,608
[ANGEL B]
They're from different realms!

433
00:20:06,525 --> 00:20:09,525
What's going on here?
Nothing's making any sense.

434
00:20:09,608 --> 00:20:11,442
[groaning]

435
00:20:11,525 --> 00:20:13,733
I can't believe
what I'm seeing.

436
00:20:13,817 --> 00:20:15,192
My dear, sweet sister.

437
00:20:16,192 --> 00:20:18,358
Uh, Miss,
from what I saw,

438
00:20:18,442 --> 00:20:20,525
they made a wonderful couple.

439
00:20:20,608 --> 00:20:23,942
And besides,
it's their romance, isn't it?

440
00:20:24,025 --> 00:20:25,942
Let's leave it to them, okay?

441
00:20:27,775 --> 00:20:29,650
[BOTH sigh]

442
00:20:29,733 --> 00:20:31,733
What do you say
we put this thing to bed for now

443
00:20:31,817 --> 00:20:33,567
and talk again
in a few days?

444
00:20:33,650 --> 00:20:34,567
Yes, I agree.

445
00:20:36,400 --> 00:20:38,108
What are they saying?

446
00:20:38,192 --> 00:20:40,525
Is it over. Or...?

447
00:20:40,608 --> 00:20:41,567
[MIYAKO]
Mm-hmm.

448
00:20:41,650 --> 00:20:43,983
Sister, stop! You're hurting me!

449
00:20:44,067 --> 00:20:45,067
-Ouch!
-[FOLCIEL] Quiet!

450
00:20:45,150 --> 00:20:46,400
[TAROUBOU grunts]

451
00:20:46,483 --> 00:20:48,858
You will never keep secrets
from me again!

452
00:20:48,942 --> 00:20:49,942
I'm sorry, Father.

453
00:20:50,025 --> 00:20:53,192
♪

454
00:20:56,608 --> 00:20:57,858
[MIYAKO]
Taroubou?

455
00:20:59,025 --> 00:21:00,692
Hello. What's your name?

456
00:21:01,775 --> 00:21:04,192
Miyako. Miyako Arata.

457
00:21:06,275 --> 00:21:07,650
I'll remember that

458
00:21:07,733 --> 00:21:10,108
♪

459
00:21:25,275 --> 00:21:26,650
So that's it.

460
00:21:26,733 --> 00:21:29,025
I never did figure out
what was going on.

461
00:21:29,108 --> 00:21:30,275
Huh.

462
00:21:30,358 --> 00:21:32,192
What are you exactly?
Be honest.

463
00:21:32,275 --> 00:21:35,275
I don't know.
I'm trying to figure that out.

464
00:21:35,358 --> 00:21:36,900
[laughter]

465
00:21:36,983 --> 00:21:38,942
[OLD MAN TENGU]
Excellently done, my friends!

466
00:21:39,025 --> 00:21:39,983
[THEO gasps]

467
00:21:40,067 --> 00:21:41,358
[THEO]
Something else is here?

468
00:21:41,442 --> 00:21:43,525
And it looks to me like
your knack of languages

469
00:21:43,608 --> 00:21:45,442
hasn't changed a bit, has it?

470
00:21:46,442 --> 00:21:48,817
-Abe no Seimei.
-[MIYAKO] Uh...

471
00:21:48,900 --> 00:21:50,692
Okay, what did
that thing just say?

472
00:21:50,775 --> 00:21:51,858
Translate!

473
00:21:51,942 --> 00:21:54,692
[MIYAKO]
Oh. He's calling me Abe.

474
00:21:54,775 --> 00:21:56,525
-Hold on.
-[KYOUICHI] What's wrong?

475
00:21:56,608 --> 00:21:58,192
-Are you okay?
-[MIYAKO groans]

476
00:21:59,858 --> 00:22:03,358
Actually, I don't know.
I'm kinda dizzy.

477
00:22:03,442 --> 00:22:04,608
Sorry.

478
00:22:04,692 --> 00:22:07,150
So... question.

479
00:22:07,233 --> 00:22:10,067
Who is Abe No Seimei?

480
00:23:42,108 --> 00:23:44,983
[wind whistling]

